	(text "PENDING per-TMC support circuitry (add in KiCad):\n\n  Per TMC2130 (U2, U3):\n    RSA, RSB: 0.1 Ω 1% 1210 (BRA, BRB to GND) — LCSC C11294\n    C_VS1:   10 µF 50V 1210 (VS bulk) — LCSC C171887 or similar\n    C_VS2:   100 nF 0402 (VS bypass) — C1525 (BASIC)\n    C_CP:    22 nF 50V 0402 (CPH-CPL) — LCSC C1532 (BASIC)\n    C_VCP:   100 nF 50V 0402 (VCP to VS)\n    C_5VOUT: 2.2 µF 0603 (5VOUT to GNDA) — LCSC C22889\n    C_VCC:   470 nF 0402 (VCC to GND)\n    R_DIAG0, R_DIAG1: 47 k 0402 pull-ups to 3V3 (open-drain) — LCSC C25803\n    R_VCC_IO: 3.3 ohm in series from 5VOUT to VCC for internal VCC supply\n               (or leave disconnected if feeding VCC externally from 3V3)\n    SPI_MODE: tied to 3V3 (hard-enable SPI mode)\n    TST_MODE: tied to GND\n    DCEN, DCIN: tied to GND (dcStep disabled)\n    DRV_ENN: to MCU or pulled low for always-enabled\n    AIN_IREF: connect to 5VOUT via 10 k / 1 k divider for internal reference,\n              or tie directly to 5VOUT for default scaling.\n\n  Shared:\n    TPS54061 PSU (see PSU sub-sheet) for 3V3 logic + TMC VCC_IO\n    SIT3088E RS-485 (U4) on USART2 (PA2/PA3) + DE on PA1\n    STM32G071 decoupling: 100 nF at each VDD + one 10 µF bulk\n\nWiring pending."
